    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Implement missing decode_ngap_nssai function for NSSAI handling\n\n### Summary\nThe NGAP layer was missing the `decode_ngap_nssai` function that is needed to properly decode NSSAI (Network Slice Selection Assistance Information) from NGAP messages. When other parts of the code tried to call this function, it would result in linker errors or undefined behavior.\n\nThis fix implements the missing `decode_ngap_nssai` function following the same pattern used elsewhere in the codebase for NSSAI decoding, and adds the necessary function declaration in the header file.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_common.c`: Added implementation of `decode_ngap_nssai` function\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_common.h`: Added function declaration for `decode_ngap_nssai`\n\nThe implementation properly decodes the SST (Single Slice Type) and SD (Slice Differentiator) fields from the ASN.1 NGAP structures into the internal `ngap_allowed_NSSAI_t` structure, following the exact same pattern used in `ngap_gNB_handlers.c` for manual NSSAI decoding.\n\n"
}